  <description><![CDATA[<p style="font-size: 16px; color: #023761;"><strong>3 nights from £1,029 (<strong>19 February 2017</strong>)</strong></p>
<p style="font-size: 16px; color: #023761;"><strong>4 nights from £1,169 (<strong>15, 22 <strong><strong>February 2017</strong></strong></strong>)</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Touch and taste nature on this varied itinerary, which brings you closer to the region’s unique seascapes through boat trips, history, local culture and delicious food. Based in the small harbour town of <a data-udi="umb://document/32d5eaa2d11e4d228a79550b66ff210f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/32d5eaa2d11e4d228a79550b66ff210f}" title="Harstad - Arctic Fjord Adventure"><strong>Harstad</strong></a>, known as Northern Norway’s culinary centre, you’ll venture out each day into the surrounding wintery landscape of this untouched part of the world, to meet the locals, discover the fascinating war history and taste the ‘food of the fjords’ in one of Harstad’s top restaurants, ‘Umami'.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>There is plenty of opportunity to create lasting memories both on land and out on the glistening fjord waters with our organised excursions, included in the price of your holiday. Of course, you’ll also have opportunity to see the Aurora Borealis on our included ‘<strong>In Search of the Northern Lights</strong>’ evening excursion, but they can also often be seen from Harstad centre.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Choose from a 3 or 4 night tour (for day-by-day details, view the Your Itinerary tab below) and head out from your 4* harbour-front hotel at Harstad each day to discover this magnificent region of fjords, mountains, northern lights and Arctic Circle adventures. <strong>Daily meals are included</strong> so the only money you’ll really need to bring is for the souvenirs you’ll want to take home!</p>
<p> </p>
<p>We have everything organised for you, all you’ll need to do is concentrate on taking in the scenery, capturing those memories on camera and enjoying your holiday! Thermal suits, hats, gloves and footwear are provided for the RIB boat sea safari.</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Harstad, known as the culinary centre of Northern Norway for its excellent selection of good restaurants, is a small, attractive harbour town with a pretty market square at its heart, set on the tip of Norway's largest coastal island, Hinnøya. The waters of the Vågsfjorden lie beyond its harbour, whilst snow-capped mountains rise dramatically behind, almost from the water's edge.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>What our guests say... </strong></p>
<p><em>"We came for the natural beauty, wildlife and Aurora and how lucky we were! The packed programme was fantastic!" </em>Ms. J. Pugh, February 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>"An excellent holiday - awesome! Views from the top of the mountain on the Snow cat excursion were stunning, the RIB boat super and the Umami dinner was amazing!"</em> Mrs. L. Du-Roe, February 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>"The whole holiday experience lived up to our expectations. The local staff and guides were extremely friendly and helpful and ensured we had the best experience of our holiday to Norway" </em>Mr. A Pickett, March 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>"An amazing experience from the beginning! I will highly recommend to friends and family" </em>Ms. F. Pont, March 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>"Superb holiday. I would not hestitate to recommend or come again. Seeing the Aurora Borealis was a bonus but the holday was even excellent before this!"</em> Mrs. S Johnson, February 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p><em>"Excellent value for money. The Umami food experienc was fantastic!", </em>Mrs. E Francis, February 2016</p>
<p> </p>
<p>Dining</p>
<p>Daily breakfast, lunch and evening meals are also all included in our tour prices. Evening meals will be taken at your hotel in Harstad or out where specified and all guests will also enjoy a fabulous lunch at Rokenes Manor and estate, renowned for its culinary traditions.</p>]]></description>
